Introduction

UNICODE is a Japanese K-pop group under XX Entertainment. They were originally formed from season 1 of ABEMA TV’s survival show Project K which aired from 2022 to 2023. After several lineup changes after the show ended, the final lineup consists of five members: Erin, Hana, Sooah, Yura, and Mio. They debuted on April 17, 2024 with the mini album "Hello, World!".
